56
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,250
Akira, what about you?

57
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:47,210
I'm going to look for a job and work normally, so don't worry.

58
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:50,260
- Would you like some dinner?
- Yeah.

59
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:10,350
When we kiss,

60
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:13,660
he always has this troubled look on his face.

61
00:05:14,130 --> 00:05:17,200
But it's not like he's rejecting me.

62
00:05:21,650 --> 00:05:24,250
And I want to touch Nishi more.

63
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:30,390
I want to see all of his expressions that I've never seen before.

64
00:05:32,970 --> 00:05:35,630
And his voices yet unheard.

65
00:05:42,230 --> 00:05:44,150
What are you doing?

66
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:51,170
Hey!

67
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,840
Come on now!

68
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:58,320
What are you going to do about job hunting?

69
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:00,720
I'm thinking of getting something nearby.

70
00:06:01,550 --> 00:06:03,600
Are you just being considerate of our parents?

71
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,800
Huh? What do you mean?

72
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:10,580
I mean, are you living life honestly with yourself?

73
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:12,970
You've always been afraid of failure.

74
00:06:12,970 --> 00:06:15,360
Sometimes you act too cautiously!

75
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:18,500
But simulations are important, right?

76
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:21,520
Sometimes it's important to just dash forward!

77
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,720
You're still young after all!

78
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:33,650
I'm someone with more imagination than most.

79
00:06:33,650 --> 00:06:39,200
However, when I imagine things I always come to my senses and give up.

80
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:45,370
In order not to fail... It's too late if

81
00:06:45,370 --> 00:06:47,170
it comes to a point where you can't undo things.

82
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:52,450
- Nishi-kun, don't you often walk along lines?
- Yeah.

83
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:55,910
If I arrive there going like this,

84
00:06:55,910 --> 00:06:59,220
I have a feeling I can reach an incredible place.

85
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,750
You don't get it?

86
00:07:02,750 --> 00:07:06,030
In any case, this white line will take me to a wonderful place!

87
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:08,540
Nishi-kun, you're a little weird you know?

88
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:10,640
I guess that's true!

89
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:13,920
Well then, I'll see you tomorrow.

90
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:16,580
Sorry for the wait!

91
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:18,040
It's okay.

92
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,310
Are you friends with that girl just now?

93
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:23,650
She's in the same lecture class as me.

94
00:07:23,650 --> 00:07:26,440
I see. Shall we go?

95
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,890
Yeah.

96
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:38,050
I can't take this anymore!

97
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:40,290
I'm tired of this report.

98
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:43,190
You have no concentration at all!

99
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,780
Let's take a break!

100
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,730
Hey!

101
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:52,860
This feels so good!

102
00:08:08,910 --> 00:08:12,110
You haven't even really progressed at all either!

103
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,640
What are you writing about anyway?

104
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:21,700
You have a lot of strange things written.

105
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:38,840
Hey! Stop, Itou!

106
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,410
Hey!

107
00:08:43,510 --> 00:08:45,710
Hey, stop it!

108
00:08:52,730 --> 00:08:55,280
You can't cross this line!

109
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:58,590
If you cross it, you will be electrocuted by one million volts of electricity!

110
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,500
Stuff like that is troubling for me!

111
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:06,540
Can't you see that I'm troubled by this?

112
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:10,950
So he really didn't like it after all.

113
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:15,310
You're always too selfish!

114
00:09:15,310 --> 00:09:17,900
The other day, you came to me outside so suddenly...

115
00:09:18,670 --> 00:09:21,940
I need to be mentally prepared for these things!

116
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:38,590
Um... So it's not that you don't like it?

117
00:09:38,590 --> 00:09:41,810
I don't like this sudden feeling at all!

118
00:09:41,810 --> 00:09:43,920
I didn't mean that.

119
00:09:47,490 --> 00:09:49,170
So basically,

120
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:55,650
