00:16:17,730 --> 00:16:21,440
[Twenty-one]
♫ My love is coming home, my love is coming home ♫

178
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:30,560
♫ My love is coming home, my love is coming home ♫

179
00:16:31,930 --> 00:16:34,250
I don't know...

180
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:35,830
You're still saying that?

181
00:16:35,830 --> 00:16:37,930
Well, that's because...

182
00:16:37,930 --> 00:16:40,690
I'm going to visit some fellow alumni next week.

183
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:45,420
I don't know where I should start from, on these decisions.

184
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:50,460
Salary and working conditions, and your companies future prospects in the business world.

185
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:53,070
If they seem like an earnest company.

186
00:16:53,070 --> 00:16:56,310
Also, if your profession has any connections to them or not.

187
00:16:56,310 --> 00:16:58,780
Why don't you think about it like that?

188
00:16:58,780 --> 00:17:01,110
That's a wake-up call...

189
00:17:01,110 --> 00:17:02,580
Huh, why?

190
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:05,940
The things you say sound like an old man.

191
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:09,080
You started smoking, too.

192
00:17:10,410 --> 00:17:12,330
Hey now.

193
00:17:15,320 --> 00:17:17,810
I can't take this anymore!

194
00:17:20,070 --> 00:17:22,130
Oh.

195
00:17:22,130 --> 00:17:25,860
Let's have you feel more like a working adult!

196
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,920
- We're going now!
- No, it's fine.

197
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,440
Stand up!

198
00:17:32,670 --> 00:17:35,060
Pull yourself together, man!

199
00:17:35,060 --> 00:17:36,870
I don't want to go!

200
00:17:38,970 --> 00:17:42,070
